article.description: — Darlinstone Dubar scored 17 points as Hofstra beat UNC Greensboro 65-53 on Saturday.
article.headline: Dubar scores 17 as Hofstra downs UNC Greensboro 65-53
article.linkText: Dubar scores 17 as Hofstra downs UNC Greensboro 65-53
article.story: LAVAL, Quebec -- — Darlinstone Dubar scored 17 points as Hofstra beat UNC Greensboro 65-53 on Saturday. Dubar added six rebounds for the Pride (5-2). Tyler Thomas was 5 of 11 shooting (2 for 6 from distance) to add 14 points. Amar'e Marshall was 2 of 4 shooting and 6 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 10 points. The Spartans (3-3) were led by Mikeal Brown-Jones, who recorded 11 points. Keondre Kennedy added 10 points and six rebounds for UNC Greensboro. Bas Leyte also recorded 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
